  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening COVID-19 emergency response for  vulnerable older women and men in  Idlib in NW Syria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project prioritises prevention, awareness raising and community sensitization focus that will help mitigate the impact of a COVID-19 outbreak when it materializes. It will focus on particularly vulnerable groups such as older women and men including older people with disabilities. Community awareness raising activities will be delivered through a mix of messaging modalities, such as use of social media, distribution of paper leaflets and flyers, use of mobile ambulances to deliver messages through loudspeaker, and training of volunteers and health workers on raising awareness and protection measure regarding COVID-19 and promoting behavioural change among the potentially affected population. For households deemed particularly vulnerable, hygiene kits for family use will be delivered, and this distribution will also be accompanied by appropriate messaging and delivery of information. A system will be established to ensure the maintenance of social contact with older people who might be isolated using phone calls, text messages and radio. Provision of awareness raising and information on COVID-19 will be made accessible to different groups of people, including older people, including older people with disabilities, through appropriate language, communication materials and age- friendly and relevant messaging. Strategies will be developed to provide Psychosocial Support for older people, including those with disabilities remotely, through training of professional counsellors and delivered through radio, telephone calls or other remote mechanisms.</narrative>
  </description>
